# Pi-hole Change Management Lab - NTP/DNS Fix

## Date
May 2, 2026

## Change Title
Resolve Pi-hole NTP DNS resolution error

## Change Type
Normal change

## System Owner
Drew

## Affected System
Pi-hole VM

## Reason for Change
Pi-hole reports an NTP error: Cannot resolve NTP server address.

## Risk Level
Low to Moderate

## Stakeholders
- Homelab administrator
- Devices using Pi-hole for DNS
- Any lab VMs depending on Pi-hole

## Impact Analysis
If DNS is misconfigured, clients may lose name resolution.
If NTP fails, logs may show incorrect timestamps.
Incorrect timestamps can make security analysis unreliable.

## Maintenance Window
Afternoon lab session, May 2, 2026

## Backout Plan
Revert Proxmox snapshot if the change breaks DNS or Pi-hole.
Restore previous DNS configuration files if edited.

## Success Criteria
- Pi-hole resolves DNS names.
- Pi-hole no longer shows the NTP resolution error.
- System time sync works.
- Client VM can resolve external domains through Pi-hole.

## Test Results

##SSH Access Correction
-During the Pi-hole change management lab, SSH was installed and confirmed running. 
-Initial login attempts using `root` and `pihole` failed or were not ideal.
-The `pihole` account was treated as an application/service account, not the preferred daily administrative login. 
-A new named administrative user, `drew`, was created for SSH access.

This follows better security practice because:
- root SSH login is avoided.
- A named user improves accountability.
- Administrative tasks can be performed with `sudo`.
- The Pi-hole service account is not used as the daily login account.
